<head>CLAMOUR</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">號叫</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>SHOUT TOGETHER in a CHAOTIC way.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for communal clamouring by a group, often expressive of dissatisfaction, is huá 嘩 / 譁.</p>
<p>2. Xiāo 囂 emphasises the loudness of the communal din, and the word is current as a reduplicated binome.</p>
<p>3. Huān 讙 is an onomatopoetic word suggesting gleeful clamour and jubilation.</p>
<p>4. Zào 噪 refers to noisiness of a flock of birds or a crowd, and written with the speech radical 譟 currently refers to the clamour of a crowd.</p>
        </div>
